{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17566872","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17566872"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":1,"answeredAt":"2025-09-29T23:50:09+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-29T23:50:09+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"18899"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"18899","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/18899"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.04,0.87,0.04,0.05,0.01]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"11632"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"80103"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"11632","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/11632"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"18899"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"65380"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"67"},{"type":"tags","id":"71"},{"type":"tags","id":"76"},{"type":"tags","id":"11260"},{"type":"tags","id":"11343"},{"type":"tags","id":"11345"},{"type":"tags","id":"12867"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"27365"},{"type":"contributions","id":"27366"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"80103","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/80103"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EA senior medical student is participating in a structured mentorship program at their hospital. During their first meeting, their assigned mentor, an experienced clinician, discusses expectations and goals for their mentoring relationship.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following best describes an effective approach to mentorship?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Providing direct supervision of clinical tasks","Offering guidance while supporting autonomous development","Providing detailed solutions to specific workplace challenges","Setting structured weekly performance targets","Sharing personal experiences without soliciting feedback"],"correctOptions":[1],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThe most effective approach to mentorship involves \u003Cstrong\u003Eoffering guidance while supporting autonomous development\u003C/strong\u003E. This creates a balanced relationship where the mentor provides support and advice while allowing the mentee to develop their own professional identity and decision-making skills.\u003C/p\u003E        \u003Cp\u003EThe incorrect approaches are:\u003C/p\u003E    \u003Cul\u003E        \u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EProviding direct supervision of clinical tasks\u003C/strong\u003E - This describes a supervisor-trainee relationship rather than mentorship, which should focus on broader professional development\u003C/li\u003E        \u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EProviding detailed solutions to specific workplace challenges\u003C/strong\u003E - This approach prevents the mentee from developing their own problem-solving skills and learning from experience\u003C/li\u003E        \u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ESetting structured weekly performance targets\u003C/strong\u003E - This reflects a performance management approach rather than mentorship, which should be more flexible and developmental\u003C/li\u003E        \u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ESharing personal experiences without soliciting feedback\u003C/strong\u003E - Effective mentorship requires two-way dialogue and active engagement from both parties\u003C/li\u003E    \u003C/ul\u003E        \u003Cp\u003EEffective mentorship relationships are characterised by mutual respect, open communication, and a focus on the mentee\u0027s holistic development. The mentor serves as a guide and resource, sharing experiences and wisdom while encouraging the mentee to develop their own professional identity and career path.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["Effective mentorship involves regular constructive feedback, guidance, and support rather than direct instruction or supervision.","Mentorship relationships should be based on mutual trust, respect, and clear expectations.","The primary goal of mentorship is to facilitate professional development and career growth through shared experience."],"references":["Medical Board of Australia. Good medical practice: a code of conduct for doctors in Australia [online]. 2020 [Cited 2025 Jan 15]. Available at: https://www.medicalboard.gov.au/codes-guidelines-policies/code-of-conduct.aspx"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"65380"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"18899"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"65380","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/65380"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2025-01-17T12:48:51+10:30","updatedAt":"2025-01-17T12:49:27+10:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"11632"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"80103"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"67","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/67"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Basic Science","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"5"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"71","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/71"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Junior","synonyms":null,"description":"Suitable for a junior, pre-clinical medical student","position":0,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"6"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"76","links":{"self":"https://a